extends Comparable<Object>
    This interface marks an object as being a CycL object.

    • Method Detail

      • cyclify

        String cyclify()
        Returns a cyclified string representation of the Cyc object. A cyclified string representation is one where constants have been prefixed with #$.
        Returns:
        a cyclified String.

      • cyclifyWithEscapeChars

        String cyclifyWithEscapeChars()
        Returns a cyclified string representation of the Cyc object. A cyclified string representation with escape chars is one where constants have been prefixed with #$ and Strings have had an escape character inserted before each character that needs to be escaped in SubL.
        Returns:
        a cyclified String with escape characters.

      • getReferencedConstants

        List getReferencedConstants()
        Returns a list of all constants refered to by this CycObject. For example, a CycConstant will return a List with itself as the value, a nart will return a list of its functor and all the constants refered to by its arguments, a CycList will do a deep search for all constants, a symbol or variable will return the empty list.
        Returns:
        a list of all constants refered to by this CycObject

      • stringApiValue

        String stringApiValue()
        Returns this object in a form suitable for use as an String api expression value.
        Returns:
        this object in a form suitable for use as an String api expression value

        this object in a form suitable for use as an CycList api expression value
